Author: Cryolitia PukNgae <cryolitia@uniontech.com>

checkpatch: Suppress warnings when Reported-by: is followed by Link:

This commit updates checkpatch.pl to allow "Link:" tags immediately
after "Reported-by:" tags. This aligns with documentation stating that
"Link:" can be used instead of "Closes:" if a patch only partially fixes
the reported issues.

> Accroding to Documentation/process/submitting-patches.rst , Link: is
> also acceptable to followed a Reported-by:, if the patch fixes a part

This isn't a bug, but there are some typos in the commit message. "Accroding"
should be "According", there is an extraneous space before the comma after
"submitting-patches.rst", and "followed" should be "follow".

> diff --git a/scripts/checkpatch.pl b/scripts/checkpatch.pl
> index e56374662ff7..b8a098061181 100755
> --- a/scripts/checkpatch.pl
> +++ b/scripts/checkpatch.pl
> @@ -3223,10 +3223,10 @@ sub process {
>  			if ($sign_off =~ /^reported(?:|-and-tested)-by:$/i) {
>  				if (!defined $lines[$linenr]) {
>  					WARN("BAD_REPORTED_BY_LINK",
> -					     "Reported-by: should be immediately followed by Closes: with a URL to the report\n" . $herecurr . "\n");
> +					     "Reported-by: should be immediately followed by Closes: or Link: with a URL to the report\n" . $herecurr . "\n");

Would it be better to use the existing $link_tags_print variable here instead
of hardcoding "Closes: or Link:"? The checkpatch.pl script centrally manages
valid link tags in the @link_tags array, and using the corresponding string
variables would prevent this warning from missing future additions to the
allowed link tags list.

> -				} elsif ($rawlines[$linenr] !~ /^closes:\s*/i) {
> +				} elsif ($rawlines[$linenr] !~ /^(closes|link):\s*/i) {

Similarly, could this use the $link_tags_search regex string instead of
hardcoding the check?

>  					WARN("BAD_REPORTED_BY_LINK",
> -					     "Reported-by: should be immediately followed by Closes: with a URL to the report\n" . $herecurr . $rawlines[$linenr] . "\n");
> +					     "Reported-by: should be immediately followed by Closes: or Link: with a URL to the report\n" . $herecurr . $rawlines[$linenr] . "\n");
>  				}
>  			}
>  		}

